@node "fera" Ferrari

Ferrari S.p.A.
==============

Chassis: Ferrari F310
Engine:  Ferrari V10
Supremo: Jean Todt
Constuctors' titles: 8

1 @{" Michael Schumacher " link "micr"}
2 @{" Eddie Irvine " link "edde"}

The season went more or less as they'd planned with Michael Schumacher
scoring three wins but still failing to reach the level of Williams.  
Suffered from mid season reliabity problems not helped by the         
rumoured detairiating relations between designer John Barnard and the 
team.

@endnode

@node "bend" "Benetton-Renault"

Benetton Formula Ltd
====================

Chassis: Benetton B196
Engine:  Renault V10
Supremo: Flavio Briatore
Constuctors' titles: 1

3 @{" Jean Alesi " link "jeai"}
4 @{" Gerhard Berger " link "gerr"}

Failed to retain their winning form of 1995 when they won eleven of
the season's seventeen races. Some claimed that this was due solely to
Michael Schumacher's departure while others claimed it was due to the
team having to work with two new drivers and take a toataly
different approach to designing a car after after almost five years with 
Michael Schumacher.

@endnode
@node "wilg" "Williams-Renault"

Williams Grand Prix Engineering
===============================

Chassis: Williams FW18
Engine:  Renault V10
Supremo: Frank 
Consructors' titles: 8

5 @{" Damon Hill " link "daml"}
6 @{" Jacques Villenuve " link "jace"}

Dominated the season winning 69% of the season's 16 races. The
combination still not 100% reliable after sufering a number of
problems with reliability (mostly for Damon Hill) although very close
to Benetton's 1995 finishing record. Renault's edge over the rest of
the engine manufactures was reduced although that didn't stop this 
superb partenship between Williams and Renault as they secured the
constructors title.

@endnode
@node "mcld" "McLaren-Mercedes"

McLaren International Ltd
=========================

Chassis: McLaren MP4/11
Engine:  Mercedes V10
Supremo: Ron Dennis
Constuctors' titles: 7

7 @{" Mika Hakkinen " link "mikn"}
8 @{" David Coulthard " link "davd"}

The dominant team of the late eighties and early ninetys failed to get
a driver on to the top step of the podiun once again despite a promsing
pre-season test in Estoril. Have had flashes of returning to the 
top throughout the year but nothing consistant and remained bottom of 
the big four.

@endnode
@node "liga" "Ligier-Mugen Honda"

Ligier Sports SA
================

Chassis: Ligier JS43
Engine:  Mugen-Honda V10
Supremo: Flavio Briatore
Constructors' titles: 0

9  @{" Olivier Panis " link "olis"}
10 @{" Pedro Paulo Diniz " link "pedz"}

With the loss of Tom Walkinshaw and Martin Brundle (who is known as a
superb devlopment driver) the team failed to retain its best of the
rest status despite Olivier Panis scoring a win in Monaco early on.
Didn't flop, in fact they stood up quiet well despite their losses
with Panis regually quallifying just outside the top 10 around the
fourteenth posistion with team mate Pedro Paulo Diniz ocasionally
matching.

@endnode
@node "jord" "Jordan-Peugeot"

Jordan Grand Prix Ltd
=====================

Chassis: Jordan 196
Engine:  Peugeot V10
Supremo: Eddie Jordan
Constructors' titles: 0

11 @{" Rubens Barrichello " link "rubo"}
12 @{" Martin Brundle " link "mare"}

With a big sponser on board this season, a works engine and some      
promising Estoril tests a lot was expected of Jordan this season but
still they failed to win a race. The problem was not with the engine -
the Peugeot was arguably the most powerful in Formula One - but with the
chassis. The team did however establish themselves as regualar top ten
qualifiers - and with improvred reliability - the fith best team in
Formula One.

@endnode
@node "ppsg" "Sauber-Ford"

PP Sauber AG
============

Chassis: Sauber C15
Engine: Ford V10
Supremo: Peter Sauber
Constructors' titles: 0

14 @{" Johnny Herbert " link "joht"}
15 @{" Heinz-Harald Frentzen " link "hein"}

As they seem to do every year, Sauber came into the championship as
dark horses, but in the end it was one of those seasons - not good,
not bad. The chassis was well engineered but the Ford V10 was in it's
first year of development but made steady progress throughout the
season.

@endnode
@node "twr1" "Arrows-Hart"

TWR Arrows F1
=============

Chassis: Footwork FA17
Engine:  Hart V8
Supremo: Tom Walkinshaw
Constructors' titles: 0

16 @{" Ricardo Rosset " link "rict"}
17 @{" Jos Verstappen " link "josn"}

Started the season well but was unable to maintain form as Tom
Walkinshaw's TWR outfit took over. The chassis' designer (Allan       
Jenkins) left for Stewert Grand Prix making understanding the chassis 
difficult and testing and development time was limited due to the     
Bridgestone tyre testing program they took up.

@endnode
@node "tyrd" "Tyrrell-Yamaha"

Tyrrell Racing Organisation
===========================

Chassis: Tyrrell 024
Engine:  Yamaha V10
Supremo: Ken Tyrrell
Constructors' titles: 1

18 @{" Ukyo Katayama " link "ukya"}
19 @{" Mika Salo " link "miko"}

Started off well but like 1995 did not have the funds to develop at
the pace of the top teams and slipped down the grid. Reliability was
apauling, the new light wieght Yamaha V10 suffering many engine
failures throughout the season.

@endnode
@node "mina" "Minardi-Ford"

Minardi Team S.p.A.
===================

Chassis: Minardi M195B
Engine:  Ford V8
Supremo: Giancarlo Minardi
Constructors' titles: 0

20 @{" Pedro Lamy " link "pedy"}
21 @{" Giancarlo Fisichella " link "giaa"}
21 @{" Tarso Marques " link "tars"}
21 @{" Giovanni Lavagi " link "gioi"}

Began the season with basicly a year old package - a slightly updated
engine and a slightly updated chassis. While they could have done
little about the engine they seem to think their previous years
chassis was a Williams beater or someting. While their 1995 chassis
was good, it needed more development and the Minardi team was
generally found towards the rear of the grid this season.

@endnode
@node "forl" "Forti-Ford"

Forti Corse SLR
===============

Chassis: FG01-95B
Engine:  Ford V8
Supremo: Guido Forti
Constructors' titles: 0

22 @{" Andrea Montermini " link "andi"}
23 @{" Luca Badoer " link "lucr"}

Few thought Forti would beat the 107% qualifying rule this year but
once their new chassis arrieved they proved capable quailyiers.
However, the team ran into financial trouble around mid season and
were never seen again after the German Grand Prix. They also got into
an ownership dispute with the Fin First group.

@endnode
@node "micr" "Micheal Schumacher"

Micheal Schumacher
==================

This Season-

Wins:			3
Pole Positions:		4
Fastest Laps:		2

Total Number of Wins:	22
Championships:		2

Moved to Ferrari this season for 'a new challenge' after winning two
championship consecutivley with Benetton. Things got better for
Schumacher through a year which included sliding off at 30mph
in Monaco. He fought back though to scored a dominant win in the wet 
in Spain and after suffering various reliability problems mid season
things began to improve during the second half of the season, scoring
a further two wins.

@endnode
@node "edde" "Eddie Irvine"

Eddie Irvine
============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0
Best Race Pos:		3rd

Total Number of Wins:	0
Career Best Race Pos:	3rd
Championships:		0

Moved to Ferrari very much as a number two driver to Michael
Schumacher. As Schumacher did the majority of the testing Irvine
struggled to get the car set up to his liking and was often a long way
from his team mate. He also suffered from more reliability problems
due to the team concerntrating its efforts on Schumacher.

@endnode
@node "jeai" "Jean Alesi"

Jean Alesi
==========

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		2
Best Race Pos:		2nd

Total Number of Wins:	1
Championships:		0

Didn't 'gell' very well into the Benetton environment after five years
at Ferrari. Many thought moving to an English team would bring out the
best in Alesi but it turned out that this wasn't going to be the case.
The team got fed up with his so called 'tantrums' that at point during
the season they repotedly locked him in their motor home. It had been
roumered that his place in the team would be taken for next season by
Giancarlo Fisichella.

@endnode
@node "gerr" "Gerhard Berger"

Gerhard Berger
==============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		1
Best Race Pos:		2nd

Total Number of Wins:	9
Championships:		0

Pre season people were tipping Berger as a dark hourse for the
championship but early races shown that they were wrong. His tall
figure interfeared with the air flow into the engine but as the season
went on things got better and Gerhard looked the quicher of the two
Benetton drivers - in the races at least, although he seemd to have a 
bit of a problem qualifying.

@endnode
@node "daml" "Damon Hill"

Damon Hill
==========

This Season-

Wins:			8
Pole Positions:		9
Fastest Laps:		5	

Total Number of Wins:	22
Championships:          1

Damon had brilliant first half of the season which included a
masterful drive in the wet at Interlargos. The second half of the
season didn't go as well however as Ferrari, McLaren, Benetton and
Jacques Villenuve all improved. Still, Damon's deffinatley a deserved
World Champion.

@endnode
@node "jace" "Jacques Villenuve

Jacques Villenuve
=================

This Season-

Wins:			4
Pole Positions:		3
Fastest Laps:		6

Total Number of Wins:	4
Championships:		0

Had a very strong debut season improving as they year went on. He came
to Formula One as the reigning Indy Car champion with a lot expected
of him - and he delived ending up bringing the championship fight down
to the last round.

@endnode
@node "mikn" "Mika Hakkinen"

Mika Hakkinen
=============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0
Best Race Pos:		3rd

Total Number of Wins:	0
Career Best Race Pos:	2nd
Championships:		0

Things looked good for Mika Hakkinen and McLaren after he sett some
blistering testing times, pre season. Right from the first race
however things failed to materialise with questions being asked about
weather or not Hakkinen was ready to return to Formula One after a big
crash the previous season. Although both Mika and the team showed     
flashes of their Estoril performaces during the season their was
nothing consistant.

@endnode
@node "davd" "David Coulthard"

David Coulthard
===============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0
Best Race Pos:		2nd

Total Number of Wins:	1
Championships:		0

McLaren was a big come down for Coulthard after almost two seasons
with Williams. In the early part of the season Coulthard developed
into team leader while Hakkinen was not at his best, but when Hakkinen
returned to form it became obvious that Couthard was not as quick.

@endnode
@node "olis" "Olivier Panis"

Olivier Panis
=============

This Season-

Wins:			1
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0

Total Number of Wins:	1
Championships:		0

The Ligier team leader enjoyed a shock win in Monaco although the rest
of the season he was fairly quiet, hanging around in mid field. Panis
claimed that he was driving a lot better this season after being
effected by the amount of speed that his previous team mate Martin
Brundle had in him, although that's a matter of opinion.

@endnode
@node "pedz" "Pedro Paulo Diniz"

Pedro Paulo Diniz
=================

This Season-

Wins:					0
Pole Positions:				0
Fastest Laps:				0
Best Race Pos:				6th

Total Number of Wins:			0
Career Best Race Pos:			6th
Championships:				0

Pedro Diniz suprised a lot of people this year with his
competitiveness compared to that of Olivier Panis. He was rarley very
far away from Panis and sometimes even outclassed him. His season will
probably be remembered for when his car burst into flames in
Argentina.

@endnode
