Apart from in Brazil when he mixed it in with the big boys, he had a
fairly consistant season, collecting points. A new atitude towards
this season ment Barrichello drove a lot better, getting less effected
by pressure.

@endnode
@node "mare" "Martin Brundle"

Martin Brundle
==============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0
Best Race Pos:		4th

Total Number of Wins:	0
Career Best Race Pos:	2nd
Championships:		0

Started the season not as he had hoped, having trouble getting used to
a car that was designed for his team mate. It didn't help matters that
cheif designer Garry Aanderson worked closely with Barrichello while
ignoring Brundle. But still, by Canada Martin had got everything
sorted and estabished himself as the quicker of the two.

@endnode
@node "joht" "Johnny Herbert"

Johnny Herbert
==============

This Season-

Wins:			0
Pole Positions:		0
Fastest Laps:		0
Best Race Pos:		3rd

Total Number of Wins:	2
Championships:		0

Johnny made progress as the season went through, getting closer and
closer to team mate Heinz-Harald Frentzecn. He had proved by the
second half of the season that he could stick with Frentzen in both
quallifying and the races.
 
@endnode
