@node "edil" "Editorial"

Editorial
=========

Welcome to the first ever issue of Racing Speed. As far as I know this
is the first and only motor sport disk magazine for the Amiga. This 
issue includes a review of the 1996 Formula One season. Future 
editions will include things like all the latest news from the world 
of motor sport, reviews of various motor sport formulas (eg F3000, 
ITC, Formula Vaxhaul Jnr etc), profiles, race reports etc. If it's to 
do with motor sport, it could well be included!!! I also welcome your 
comments on Racing Speed (maybe you'd like to see a pen pal or letters 
section) and encourage you to send in your atrticles (especially season 
reviews)!!!

Finaly I'd just like to say I hope you enjoy reading Racing Speed and
appologise in advance for any mistakes that you may find.


/      |_ |_
\ / /\ |  |
/ \ \/ |  |

N.B. Some of the back runners Career Best Finishing Pos: might not be
     100% accurate.

@endnode
@node "hows" "Submitting Articles"

Submitting Articles
===================

I can't encourage you enough to mail me your articles. Just as long as
they are motor sport related and a similar article has not already
been submitted, your article will be included in the next issue. For
details of where to mail your articles to see the next section.

Articles should be submitted in ASCII form, with a page width of no
more than 70 columns and should be incuded in a message - not sent as
a sepperate file attched to the message as many systems will reject
these.

@endnode
